title: 'NASCAR Race Hub' asks if Duels could have similar ending to the Clash
text:
Feb 21, 2017 at 1:48p ET 0Shares 
After such an exciting finish to the Advance Auto Parts Clash, ‘NASCAR Race Hub’ asked Bobby Labonte and Drew Blickensderfer if they’d make a similar move that Denny Hamlin did to end a Can-Am Duel race Thursday night at 7 p.m. on FS1. 
You might be wondering why anyone would make a big move to win a Can-Am Duel race. Especially, when the payoff is a second-row starting spot. 
But, wait! 
The new NASCAR race format now means that the winner of the Can-Am Duel races gets 10 regular-season points. 
Is it worth potentially smashing up a Daytona 500 car on Thursday for a chance at 10 points? 
Find out Labonte and Blickensderfer’s thoughts above.
